I received a narrative summary of the quest.

82
00:03:29,230 --> 00:03:31,131
This is a document generated by the writer

83
00:03:31,251 --> 00:03:32,652
after a quest pitch is agreed to.

84
00:03:33,212 --> 00:03:34,313
With a main quest like this,

85
00:03:34,493 --> 00:03:36,634
there have already been lead and director level meetings

86
00:03:36,934 --> 00:03:38,575
to discuss the major goals, gameplay,

87
00:03:38,655 --> 00:03:39,596
and story of the quest.

88
00:03:40,837 --> 00:03:41,937
Starting from the narrative summary,

89
00:03:42,017 --> 00:03:43,318
I break down the steps of the quest

90
00:03:43,358 --> 00:03:45,860
into the early beat sheet or design document.

91
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:48,521
During the process, I may add, change,

92
00:03:48,901 --> 00:03:51,203
or tweak the events spelled out in the narrative summary

93
00:03:51,623 --> 00:03:53,224
and add gameplay to clarify goals

94
00:03:53,304 --> 00:03:55,065
with the approval of leads and direction.

95
00:03:56,142 --> 00:03:58,084
Once that early design doc beat sheet is approved,

96
00:03:58,404 --> 00:03:59,605
I start paper prototyping.

97
00:04:04,570 --> 00:04:05,991
This is a good time to mention that I'm gonna try

98
00:04:06,031 --> 00:04:07,913
to keep this talk as spoiler light as I can,

99
00:04:09,635 --> 00:04:11,096
but let me give you a little bit of context.

100
00:04:11,716 --> 00:04:13,798
In this quest, Aloy goes to an old world bunker

101
00:04:13,918 --> 00:04:15,300
in search of a backup of Gaia,

102
00:04:15,460 --> 00:04:17,962
the AI designed to control the terraforming process of Earth.

103
00:04:18,403 --> 00:04:19,083
That's this bunker.

104
00:04:20,138 --> 00:04:24,460
As Aloy enters the facility, she enters a central hallway where she finds a blockage

105
00:04:24,540 --> 00:04:25,681
caused by water and time.

106
00:04:26,141 --> 00:04:29,182
She'll need to get around that blockage to reach an inner gene lock door.

107
00:04:29,963 --> 00:04:33,304
Nearby is an old communications center containing a puzzle to unlock a door.

108
00:04:34,355 --> 00:04:38,618
Past that locked door are stairs down to a flooded residential area that we swim through.

109
00:04:39,278 --> 00:04:42,581
At the end of that swim is an office and a way back up to level one.

110
00:04:43,241 --> 00:04:47,845
Back on level one, Aloy enters the second gene locked door and there's a space that

111
00:04:47,865 --> 00:04:51,667
we call the recluse chamber and there's a big cinematic there that I'm not going to

112
00:04:51,707 --> 00:04:52,068
talk about.

113
00:04:54,825 --> 00:04:57,087
And that's where some bad dudes show up.

114
00:04:57,407 --> 00:04:58,527
She finds what she's looking for.

115
00:04:58,928 --> 00:05:02,429
The chamber is destroyed and she falls into a lower level,

116
00:05:03,290 --> 00:05:05,291
like an old sort of section of the bunker

117
00:05:05,331 --> 00:05:06,211
that's like a boiler room.

118
00:05:06,632 --> 00:05:08,993
And there she'll need to swim to escape

119
00:05:09,213 --> 00:05:11,374
while being pursued by some new machines called Spectres.

120
00:05:14,676 --> 00:05:15,937
With that paper design in hand,

121
00:05:15,957 --> 00:05:18,618
we're ready to go to the skeleton quest phase,

122
00:05:18,678 --> 00:05:20,139
making the initial block out of the bunker.

123
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,700
But what is a skeleton quest?

124
00:05:23,765 --> 00:05:27,006
The simplest version of Skeleton Quest is one where the player can walk between various

125
00:05:27,026 --> 00:05:31,068
locations on the map and there are simple pop-up text windows that appear and describe

126
00:05:31,108 --> 00:05:31,628
what happens.

127
00:05:32,328 --> 00:05:36,570
This helps give a sense of pacing and flow for quests that take place primarily in the

128
00:05:36,650 --> 00:05:37,270
overworld map.

129
00:05:38,291 --> 00:05:42,192
A Skeleton Quest for a large interior like this is often more complicated, it's more

130
00:05:42,232 --> 00:05:44,733
work because you need to create a block mesh of the entire bunker.

131
00:05:45,783 --> 00:05:47,324
With a skeleton quest in the overworld,

132
00:05:47,364 --> 00:05:50,486
you often have some natural features to work with or around.

133
00:05:50,907 --> 00:05:52,948
Without that, it's important to have some look

134
00:05:53,188 --> 00:05:54,629
at the bunker early on,

135
00:05:55,229 --> 00:05:57,410
some assistance from a team like Concept Art.

136
00:05:59,492 --> 00:06:01,033
Here's an early piece from Concept Art

137
00:06:01,053 --> 00:06:03,094
suggesting the layers of construction of the bunker

138
00:06:03,454 --> 00:06:04,675
based on my paper designs.

139
00:06:05,175 --> 00:06:06,216
Notice the flooded floors

140
00:06:06,416 --> 00:06:07,997
and the older levels of the facility.

141
00:06:09,598 --> 00:06:11,079
They had this very interesting idea

142
00:06:11,099 --> 00:06:13,200
to wrap the facility around the innermost area,

143
00:06:13,580 --> 00:06:14,481
the recluse chamber.

144
00:06:15,912 --> 00:06:18,313
In that chamber, Aloy finds the Recluse Processor.

145
00:06:18,773 --> 00:06:20,234
This is a machine, potentially,

146
00:06:20,254 --> 00:06:23,036
that holds the copy of Gaia that Aloy's looking for,

147
00:06:23,356 --> 00:06:24,897
so it's her ultimate goal in this quest.

148
00:06:25,177 --> 00:06:27,799
But it also must serve a variety of other complex needs

149
00:06:28,319 --> 00:06:29,840
that I'm gonna show you here in a moment.

