255
00:10:38,744 --> 00:10:40,505
But you'll see how that space changed over time.

256
00:10:42,446 --> 00:10:44,687
Here within the swimscape, there is an office.

257
00:10:45,148 --> 00:10:47,569
This is Travis Tate's office, if you know Travis Tate.

258
00:10:48,469 --> 00:10:49,970
And the idea is that in this space,

259
00:10:50,010 --> 00:10:52,091
we would find a story moment, another cinematic

260
00:10:52,151 --> 00:10:52,772
or a hologram.

261
00:10:54,417 --> 00:10:55,517
And by going through his office,

262
00:10:55,558 --> 00:10:57,819
we'd be able to get into that hallway you just saw there,

263
00:10:58,540 --> 00:11:00,722
which will allow us to climb back up to level one,

264
00:11:00,882 --> 00:11:02,403
to the gene lock door, to our goal.

265
00:11:04,785 --> 00:11:07,207
So you might know in the final game, Fire Gleam.

266
00:11:07,647 --> 00:11:09,409
This is the very first version of Fire Gleam.

267
00:11:09,449 --> 00:11:11,850
We had these sort of placed C4 explosives.

268
00:11:15,573 --> 00:11:17,715
You'll see that iterate a few times through this as well.

269
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:32,532
You'll see here that Aloy is self-talking.

270
00:11:32,672 --> 00:11:35,414
She says something like, comments that she should go up this ladder.

271
00:11:35,815 --> 00:11:38,377
That's how we handle self-talk in the beginning of development.

272
00:11:38,837 --> 00:11:43,181
They don't want us writing things that seem fictional or seem like actual dialogue because

273
00:11:43,201 --> 00:11:45,463
that can get confusing as the state of development we're in.

274
00:11:46,027 --> 00:11:48,148
So what we do in these early versions of the quest

275
00:11:48,448 --> 00:11:50,530
is we put in self-tuck that's important

276
00:11:50,590 --> 00:11:53,052
for direction of the player that's kind of like that.

277
00:11:53,232 --> 00:11:55,794
Like Aloy comments that she should look up above her.

278
00:11:55,814 --> 00:11:58,256
Aloy comments that she should go down that hallway.

279
00:11:58,356 --> 00:11:58,876
Stuff like that.

280
00:12:01,058 --> 00:12:02,619
So now we enter the second gene lock door

281
00:12:02,659 --> 00:12:04,500
and we go into the recluse chamber.

282
00:12:07,222 --> 00:12:09,044
So this room holds the recluse processor

283
00:12:09,084 --> 00:12:09,944
I talked about earlier,

284
00:12:10,064 --> 00:12:11,566
which is this giant spider looking thingy.

285
00:12:12,562 --> 00:12:13,784
And the giant spider looking thingy

286
00:12:14,124 --> 00:12:15,947
is an AI testing apparatus.

287
00:12:16,067 --> 00:12:19,332
It was used to test old versions of Hades

288
00:12:19,372 --> 00:12:20,734
against old versions of Gaia.

289
00:12:20,795 --> 00:12:23,519
So that's why Aloy thinks she can find a copy of Gaia here.

290
00:12:25,383 --> 00:12:27,044
These are cinematic placeholders right now

291
00:12:27,144 --> 00:12:29,986
because we didn't actually know what those were gonna be.

292
00:12:30,366 --> 00:12:31,987
We didn't really know how to handle something

293
00:12:32,007 --> 00:12:34,809
that wasn't a cinematic but not a gameplay interaction.

294
00:12:35,229 --> 00:12:37,470
So for the time being, we treated them as cinematics.

295
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:42,013
But we wanted to do these semi-interactive moments

296
00:12:42,053 --> 00:12:44,134
where Aloy's messing with holographic UI.

297
00:12:44,894 --> 00:12:46,415
This is an early version of the spider

298
00:12:46,455 --> 00:12:47,396
where we climbed on it.

299
00:12:48,977 --> 00:12:50,398
This is not something we ended up shipping with,

300
00:12:50,418 --> 00:12:51,758
but I still think it's a really cool idea.

301
00:12:53,726 --> 00:12:56,429
Aloy now gets the copy of Guy out of this kernel.

302
00:12:56,449 --> 00:12:58,271
There's a cinematic there that I'm skipping over

303
00:12:58,291 --> 00:13:00,053
because it's super spoilery.

304
00:13:01,214 --> 00:13:02,876
And then this bad guy shows up.

305
00:13:03,536 --> 00:13:05,358
And he's here to choke the life out of you.

306
00:13:05,979 --> 00:13:07,781
He's this slow moving humanoid guy

307
00:13:07,801 --> 00:13:08,982
that chases you around the space.

308
00:13:09,383 --> 00:13:11,104
And the only way Aloy can escape this space

309
00:13:11,124 --> 00:13:13,447
is by dropping the spider, getting it to fall down.

310
00:13:14,445 --> 00:13:16,307
We do that by shooting weak points on the spider.

311
00:13:17,608 --> 00:13:18,669
After a certain amount of weak points,

312
00:13:18,689 --> 00:13:20,471
there's a phase transition cinematic,

313
00:13:20,871 --> 00:13:22,052
and then you shoot some more weak points

314
00:13:22,312 --> 00:13:23,934
while trying to get away from this guy,

315
00:13:24,294 --> 00:13:27,457
and then eventually that opens up an interaction

316
00:13:27,517 --> 00:13:28,698
with the Recluse processor

317
00:13:28,738 --> 00:13:30,660
where it kind of drops down to a lower level,

318
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:33,002
and you use a use location underneath it

319
00:13:33,042 --> 00:13:35,744
to trigger a cinematic where the spider

320
00:13:35,964 --> 00:13:37,626
falls down through the floor and you with it.

321
00:13:37,926 --> 00:13:38,987
So that's this right here.

322
00:13:47,618 --> 00:13:49,640
So now we fall into the old part of the bunker,

323
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:51,200
kind of this boiler room area

324
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:52,801
where we need to swim to escape.

325
00:13:53,922 --> 00:13:55,843
This has one of my favorite early parts

326
00:13:55,863 --> 00:13:56,803
of the levels hackery.

327
00:13:57,544 --> 00:14:00,245
We had no idea what the specters were gonna look like,

328
00:14:00,285 --> 00:14:01,406
this new kind of machine,

329
00:14:01,586 --> 00:14:02,766
and indeed it would take years

330
00:14:02,886 --> 00:14:04,867
before we got even a mock-up of one.

331
00:14:05,488 --> 00:14:08,089
So what I used instead was human enemies

332
00:14:08,109 --> 00:14:10,230
from the first game with laser beams attached to their faces.

333
00:14:12,053 --> 00:14:13,574
We wanted to build something that was kind of like

334
00:14:13,614 --> 00:14:14,495
a stealth arena.

335
00:14:14,555 --> 00:14:17,297
We wanted this vibe of like, you're sneaking around

336
00:14:17,317 --> 00:14:18,578
and there's these really dangerous things

337
00:14:18,598 --> 00:14:19,738
that are sort of like turrets

338
00:14:19,938 --> 00:14:21,399
that are scanning around for you.

339
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:23,821
And if they spot you, then they shoot you.

340
00:14:23,861 --> 00:14:25,722
And so you really have to stay out of their line of sight.

341
00:14:26,082 --> 00:14:28,424
This would also kind of teach you about stealth and water

342
00:14:28,644 --> 00:14:29,384
and how that works.

343
00:14:29,724 --> 00:14:31,746
But we actually didn't know how any of that worked.

344
00:14:32,126 --> 00:14:35,628
So it took a while to figure out how, say for example,

345
00:14:36,048 --> 00:14:38,690
machines could or couldn't spot you underwater.

346
00:14:39,671 --> 00:14:41,172
But these were our early experiments.

347
00:14:42,662 --> 00:14:45,066
You can also see we have some pullable vents in here

348
00:14:45,146 --> 00:14:48,031
for underwater that are very early versions.

349
00:14:48,571 --> 00:14:51,316
There's also a pullcaster interaction right here

350
00:14:51,356 --> 00:14:53,219
that survives even until the final version

351
00:14:54,081 --> 00:14:56,745
where you get out of the water to pull open this vent.

352
00:15:13,310 --> 00:15:17,053
And then in this final section, there's something kind of like a gauntlet where you'd swim into

353
00:15:17,093 --> 00:15:19,075
a big space where you think you're home free.

354
00:15:19,856 --> 00:15:24,740
And one of these specters would blast open the ceiling and rain fire down upon you.

355
00:15:24,780 --> 00:15:30,045
So you'd have to swim really quickly through the fire, through the strafing fire.

356
00:15:30,065 --> 00:15:31,126
There you go.

357
00:15:31,166 --> 00:15:31,767
That's that guy.

358
00:15:33,208 --> 00:15:34,309
But he can't actually shoot at you.

359
00:15:34,329 --> 00:15:35,390
He has no idea what's going on.

360
00:15:36,411 --> 00:15:37,592
He's like, you're in water?

361
00:15:37,832 --> 00:15:38,493
What's water?

362
00:15:41,117 --> 00:15:42,118
And then here at the end of the level,

363
00:15:42,138 --> 00:15:44,298
there's another one of these breach charge interactions

364
00:15:44,378 --> 00:15:46,879
and blowing this door open allows Aloy to escape.

365
00:15:50,001 --> 00:15:51,601
So, just for ease of reference,

366
00:15:51,721 --> 00:15:54,142
I want to quickly label some of the areas of the bunker

367
00:15:54,282 --> 00:15:55,082
that we just looked at,

368
00:15:55,403 --> 00:15:56,703
because we'll be talking a lot about them.

369
00:15:57,623 --> 00:15:59,204
So first we have the central hallway,

370
00:16:00,124 --> 00:16:01,085
the communications center,

371
00:16:02,885 --> 00:16:04,906
the swim labs, this area here,

372
00:16:06,167 --> 00:16:07,047
the recluse chamber,

373
00:16:08,127 --> 00:16:09,348
and lastly the swim escape.

374
00:16:12,685 --> 00:16:15,307
Okay, so once the skeleton is submitted and approved,

375
00:16:15,827 --> 00:16:17,748
we now proceed to turn the skeleton quest

376
00:16:17,788 --> 00:16:19,149
into what we call a first playable.

377
00:16:19,569 --> 00:16:20,469
That's a bit confusing, right,

378
00:16:20,489 --> 00:16:21,910
because that was clearly playable, right?

379
00:16:23,391 --> 00:16:26,592
But there are a few key differences

380
00:16:26,632 --> 00:16:28,593
between what's a skeleton and what's first playable.

381
00:16:29,534 --> 00:16:30,895
So what does constitute first playable?

382
00:16:31,735 --> 00:16:34,356
It's about bringing all gameplay to a representative state.

383
00:16:34,977 --> 00:16:36,717
Any gameplay in the skeleton that we explain

384
00:16:36,757 --> 00:16:39,879
with a text box or that needs further development

385
00:16:39,919 --> 00:16:41,860
to actually look something like what we intend,

386
00:16:42,737 --> 00:16:44,678
that's what actually we need to transition

387
00:16:44,718 --> 00:16:45,539
into proper gameplay.

388
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:48,262
The first playable's the first version of the quest

389
00:16:48,282 --> 00:16:49,883
where we'll start playtesting externally.

390
00:16:50,664 --> 00:16:52,826
And thinking back on the skeleton quest video I just showed,

391
00:16:52,846 --> 00:16:54,447
there are a few areas that we really wanted

392
00:16:54,467 --> 00:16:57,610
to spend time developing up to representative quality.

393
00:16:59,358 --> 00:17:00,539
starting with the communications center.

394
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:02,420
We didn't feel that the space

395
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:04,381
and the puzzle placeholder inside were representative

396
00:17:04,421 --> 00:17:05,582
of what we really wanted to do.

397
00:17:06,202 --> 00:17:08,343
We knew we wanted to do a new kind of power puzzle,

398
00:17:08,943 --> 00:17:10,124
a follow-up to the multi-lock,

399
00:17:10,224 --> 00:17:12,045
but we didn't really know what that was yet.

400
00:17:12,105 --> 00:17:12,765
We still didn't.

401
00:17:13,906 --> 00:17:15,507
And the space itself also had to tell

402
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:16,827
kind of a specific story.

403
00:17:17,828 --> 00:17:19,108
And so we relied on concept art

404
00:17:19,128 --> 00:17:20,169
to kind of help us get there.

405
00:17:21,523 --> 00:17:23,685
This room is the one point of communication

406
00:17:23,845 --> 00:17:24,665
in and out of the bunker.

407
00:17:25,106 --> 00:17:26,447
Because of the dangerous experiments

408
00:17:26,487 --> 00:17:27,468
conducted in this facility,

409
00:17:27,828 --> 00:17:29,469
no unsecured data could come in or out.

410
00:17:30,210 --> 00:17:31,891
We wanted to tell that story while at the same time

411
00:17:31,951 --> 00:17:34,393
forcing the player to engage with a new type of power puzzle.

412
00:17:35,974 --> 00:17:37,676
So you see there's this object marked

413
00:17:37,716 --> 00:17:39,937
like power facility up there at the top for instance.

414
00:17:42,419 --> 00:17:42,559
So.

415
00:17:42,579 --> 00:17:43,840
Oh.

416
00:17:45,842 --> 00:17:46,282
What's this?

417
00:17:47,003 --> 00:17:48,364
Some kind of command center?

418
00:17:49,212 --> 00:17:51,752
So you can see that I reworked the space to be based on this

419
00:17:51,792 --> 00:17:55,614
kind of curved concept with this console, with this screen. And

420
00:17:55,694 --> 00:17:58,194
we tried out some new puzzle concepts in here, new uses of

421
00:17:58,214 --> 00:18:00,815
the pull caster where we have these pullable boxes that you

422
00:18:00,835 --> 00:18:03,176
can yoink around the space using the pull caster that will allow

423
00:18:03,216 --> 00:18:06,537
you to climb up to higher spaces. There's also this object

424
00:18:06,577 --> 00:18:09,818
here that's kind of like a back up generator and we wanted to

425
00:18:09,898 --> 00:18:12,079
try some kind of novel interaction here where you'd

426
00:18:12,239 --> 00:18:14,779
override it maybe with a mini game or some kind of thing like

427
00:18:14,820 --> 00:18:17,280
this. But for the moment it's just a hack point.

428
00:18:20,443 --> 00:18:22,163
Early on, we thought that it'd be really cool

429
00:18:22,203 --> 00:18:24,184
to use this screen that you see over here on the wall

430
00:18:24,264 --> 00:18:26,504
and show you that when you powered this thing up,

431
00:18:26,544 --> 00:18:28,805
that there might be like a giant antenna outside

432
00:18:28,845 --> 00:18:31,786
in the world that would extend and change the world outside.

433
00:18:32,166 --> 00:18:34,146
But it's something that just sort of fell

434
00:18:34,166 --> 00:18:35,027
to the wayside over time.

435
00:18:35,067 --> 00:18:36,687
It was something too expensive for us

436
00:18:36,727 --> 00:18:38,087
to mock up in any meaningful way.

437
00:18:39,868 --> 00:18:42,028
So when you power the room up, now we get the cinematic.

438
00:18:45,583 --> 00:18:47,324
The next area we wanted to make some changes to

439
00:18:47,364 --> 00:18:49,266
was the lower level flooded residential area,

440
00:18:49,686 --> 00:18:51,708
and we really wanted to execute on a specific vision.

441
00:18:52,548 --> 00:18:54,330
We had an idea early on to try to achieve

442
00:18:54,370 --> 00:18:57,052
a unique cave diving feeling for the lab swim area.

443
00:18:57,672 --> 00:18:59,494
Bunkers in Horizon Zero Dawn have kind of

444
00:18:59,514 --> 00:19:01,455
a cave-like aesthetic, so cave diving

445
00:19:01,475 --> 00:19:02,536
seems to make a lot of sense.

446
00:19:04,278 --> 00:19:07,139
We needed to add lighting to get a representative feel

447
00:19:07,199 --> 00:19:08,700
of the gameplay, so that's something we did.

448
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:11,082
We did some very early rough lighting in here,

449
00:19:11,502 --> 00:19:13,943
and we experimented with the first version

450
00:19:13,963 --> 00:19:16,224
of a light on the player, which you'll see as well.

451
00:19:17,065 --> 00:19:19,246
We also got some help from concept art here

452
00:19:19,386 --> 00:19:20,427
to get a sense of the look.

453
00:19:21,167 --> 00:19:24,129
Here are some mood boards and explorations

454
00:19:24,149 --> 00:19:26,330
of what this cave diving concept would look like,

455
00:19:26,370 --> 00:19:27,150
what it would feel like.

456
00:19:28,935 --> 00:19:30,417
This piece was really my North Star.

457
00:19:31,278 --> 00:19:33,079
I tried really hard to achieve this look

458
00:19:33,119 --> 00:19:34,260
during the process of development

459
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:35,321
because I thought it was so cool.

460
00:19:36,663 --> 00:19:38,845
So, here's an iteration where we lit

461
00:19:38,885 --> 00:19:40,226
the swimming area very darkly.

462
00:19:40,566 --> 00:19:42,328
You can also see that there's a light on Aloy

463
00:19:42,368 --> 00:19:43,169
that's on her arm.

464
00:19:44,110 --> 00:19:46,112
We also added this like floating debris

465
00:19:46,132 --> 00:19:47,253
and all this stuff that you could kind of

466
00:19:47,293 --> 00:19:48,554
move around the space because we were trying

467
00:19:48,574 --> 00:19:49,675
to hit this vibe, right?

468
00:19:49,715 --> 00:19:50,716
We were trying to get this feeling.

469
00:19:51,096 --> 00:19:52,578
You'll also notice that we cut the puzzle.

470
00:19:53,380 --> 00:19:57,423
It just wasn't that important here. It wasn't something we wanted to add more friction to this space.

471
00:19:57,743 --> 00:20:01,185
We just wanted to get you used to swimming inside and that seemed frictional enough.

472
00:20:02,686 --> 00:20:09,271
It was also really important to teach you about swimming in interiors because later on during the escape you need to know how to do that already.

473
00:20:11,913 --> 00:20:15,395
You'll see that there's a bit of weird stuff here where the light is reflecting on the surface of the water.

474
00:20:15,455 --> 00:20:17,537
That's just some early versions of this.

475
00:20:26,257 --> 00:20:28,698
So this puzzle that's in the other space now,

476
00:20:28,819 --> 00:20:30,200
instead of finding a valve wheel,

477
00:20:30,420 --> 00:20:32,361
there's a treasure chest basically in the same spot.

478
00:20:32,381 --> 00:20:34,403
So we just kept the same space.

479
00:20:36,344 --> 00:20:37,605
So pretty much the same thing here.

480
00:20:39,246 --> 00:20:40,647
The next area we wanted to focus on

481
00:20:40,687 --> 00:20:42,308
was the recluse chamber boss battle.

482
00:20:44,630 --> 00:20:47,112
We wanted to add in the first representative spider model.

483
00:20:47,412 --> 00:20:49,013
We felt it was really important to give you

484
00:20:49,554 --> 00:20:50,975
the actual real thing,

485
00:20:51,335 --> 00:20:53,937
because my version was this really weird tinker toy spider.

486
00:20:55,585 --> 00:20:57,946
We wanted to add the pull caster into the boss fight.

487
00:20:58,006 --> 00:20:59,747
This boss fight was really more like a puzzle,

488
00:20:59,787 --> 00:21:02,527
so we wanted to add the new primary puzzle tool

489
00:21:02,587 --> 00:21:03,708
into it to see if that would work.

490
00:21:04,788 --> 00:21:06,028
We cut the climbing on the spider

491
00:21:06,169 --> 00:21:08,049
in favor of adding a sort of tutorial moment

492
00:21:08,109 --> 00:21:09,730
because now we needed to teach you

493
00:21:09,770 --> 00:21:11,310
that you needed to pull these weak points.

494
00:21:12,390 --> 00:21:13,791
That's why we needed a tutorial moment.

495
00:21:14,870 --> 00:21:17,011
and we moved the weak points to the walls from the spider.

496
00:21:17,471 --> 00:21:19,251
In the earliest versions of people playing this,

497
00:21:19,271 --> 00:21:21,252
they just constantly looked up at the spider the whole time

498
00:21:21,292 --> 00:21:23,272
and just ran around it and they never looked at the dude.

499
00:21:23,873 --> 00:21:26,133
So we thought, let's move the weak points out into the space

500
00:21:26,173 --> 00:21:27,694
and so you have to look around the space more

501
00:21:27,734 --> 00:21:28,894
so you see the bad guy.

502
00:21:30,814 --> 00:21:33,355
We also got this piece of concept art at this point

503
00:21:33,435 --> 00:21:35,936
and this was like the one before, kind of my North Star.

504
00:21:35,956 --> 00:21:37,376
This is the thing I wanted to try to hit

505
00:21:37,396 --> 00:21:38,836
because I thought this was an awesome vibe.

506
00:21:40,637 --> 00:21:42,277
So here's the very first playable version

507
00:21:42,297 --> 00:21:43,758
of that animating recluse spider.

508
00:21:45,962 --> 00:21:48,584
You'll also notice that the cage around here is not a sphere.

509
00:21:48,604 --> 00:21:51,747
That was extremely hard to mock up, so I used this kind of cage shape in the beginning.

510
00:22:03,572 --> 00:22:06,774
So when you use this console, we now kick in this tutorial moment that I was talking

