00:23:54,814 --> 00:23:56,235
So I start to work on some other things.

560
00:23:58,595 --> 00:24:00,016
So one of the other quests that I work on

561
00:24:00,076 --> 00:24:01,996
was a quest called Seeds of the Past,

562
00:24:02,197 --> 00:24:03,717
which is related to the AI Demeter.

563
00:24:05,145 --> 00:24:07,768
Early playtesting told us that the puzzles in Death's Door were too simple.

564
00:24:08,188 --> 00:24:11,271
We knew that. We're still trying to figure out this new power puzzle mechanic.

565
00:24:12,612 --> 00:24:18,678
In response to that, we played around with a new power puzzle concept called the Charged Spear that I want to show you.

566
00:24:20,663 --> 00:24:23,405
So, I was telling you about that tutorial moment earlier.

567
00:24:23,545 --> 00:24:25,787
This is something that a new designer from Eidos, Montreal

568
00:24:25,827 --> 00:24:28,349
coming in taught me about that they have there,

569
00:24:28,409 --> 00:24:30,010
which is the idea of a nugget puzzle.

570
00:24:30,750 --> 00:24:33,452
So in open world games, it's really tough to teach puzzles

571
00:24:33,593 --> 00:24:35,234
and to get players to remember puzzles

572
00:24:35,294 --> 00:24:37,115
because we don't know how long it's been

573
00:24:37,195 --> 00:24:38,396
since you've seen the puzzle.

574
00:24:38,896 --> 00:24:40,097
We were playing around with using this

575
00:24:40,137 --> 00:24:41,078
in the tall neck as well.

576
00:24:42,019 --> 00:24:43,639
So I didn't know if you had done that before.

577
00:24:43,699 --> 00:24:46,040
I didn't know if you had learned about this puzzle concept.

578
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:51,021
So I needed a really small little instance of it to either teach it to you or to get

579
00:24:51,061 --> 00:24:52,001
you to remember it.

580
00:24:52,361 --> 00:24:53,482
And that's what this is here.

581
00:24:53,542 --> 00:24:54,382
It's called a nugget.

582
00:24:54,822 --> 00:24:58,563
Basically, you come into this room, you see a charging station, you charge up your spear

583
00:24:58,583 --> 00:25:02,284
with it, you go over to this receptacle, you plug it in, the energy goes into it and it

584
00:25:02,424 --> 00:25:03,084
unlocks the door.

585
00:25:03,624 --> 00:25:09,367
Same concept in here. There's a receptacle on that opposite wall. You need to charge up your spear using that battery in the other room

586
00:25:09,687 --> 00:25:13,349
You need to cross over this space and you need to plug in your spear to power up this room

587
00:25:14,009 --> 00:25:19,532
Now the twist is the the aspect of this that you'll notice that's new is there's a thin layer of water on the floor

588
00:25:20,072 --> 00:25:25,115
The idea of the charge spear was you can carry around this charge in your spear so long as you don't touch water

589
00:25:25,875 --> 00:25:27,736
If you touch water, the charge dissipates,

590
00:25:28,556 --> 00:25:30,417
and then you have to go back and get a new charge.

591
00:25:30,757 --> 00:25:33,197
There's also still this aspect of yoinking stuff

592
00:25:33,217 --> 00:25:34,738
around the room using the pullcaster

593
00:25:34,778 --> 00:25:36,098
to make a bridge for yourself

594
00:25:36,138 --> 00:25:37,659
to be able to cross across the space.

595
00:25:40,819 --> 00:25:42,660
So the player's gonna go back over here to the battery,

596
00:25:42,940 --> 00:25:45,161
gonna plug in her spear, get a charge in it,

597
00:25:45,381 --> 00:25:46,421
and then come back to the room.

598
00:25:51,983 --> 00:25:53,843
But just as an example, you'll see here

599
00:25:53,883 --> 00:25:55,143
what happens when you jump in the water.

600
00:25:56,876 --> 00:25:57,737
The charge dissipates.

601
00:25:59,077 --> 00:26:01,638
Our design director, he didn't love that version of it.

602
00:26:01,859 --> 00:26:03,659
He wanted a version where we had deeper water,

603
00:26:03,779 --> 00:26:04,680
which is what this is.

604
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,541
He felt like the thin layer of water

605
00:26:06,621 --> 00:26:09,022
just felt too much like a children's game,

606
00:26:09,062 --> 00:26:10,903
you know, like don't touch the lava on the floor.

607
00:26:11,203 --> 00:26:12,984
It doesn't feel heroic to have to avoid

608
00:26:13,024 --> 00:26:14,425
like a half inch of water on the floor.

609
00:26:15,025 --> 00:26:16,846
So we tried this version with deeper water.

610
00:26:17,806 --> 00:26:19,747
Also, this is the first version of the hologram

611
00:26:19,787 --> 00:26:21,768
you can see that goes in here when you power up the room.

612
00:26:21,988 --> 00:26:23,289
I thought it was super cool that the hologram,

613
00:26:23,329 --> 00:26:24,850
people were all talking to each other underwater.

614
00:26:27,425 --> 00:26:30,386
So, the art passes start coming in here.

615
00:26:31,827 --> 00:26:32,887
What happens during the art pass,

616
00:26:32,947 --> 00:26:35,168
I receive from the artist new art files

617
00:26:35,208 --> 00:26:36,489
that I have to hook up into the game.

618
00:26:36,949 --> 00:26:38,250
They don't do this because if they did it,

619
00:26:38,290 --> 00:26:39,170
it would break a bunch of stuff.

620
00:26:40,111 --> 00:26:41,731
I compare my block out to the new art

621
00:26:41,791 --> 00:26:43,232
because things always shift around,

622
00:26:43,832 --> 00:26:46,113
and so I have to move my objects around in the space,

623
00:26:47,154 --> 00:26:50,095
and I have to delete my block mesh stuff,

624
00:26:50,135 --> 00:26:51,356
kind of like one piece at a time

625
00:26:51,376 --> 00:26:53,257
to make sure that it's accurately represented.

626
00:26:55,020 --> 00:26:57,487
Typically we have two art passes and then a lighting pass.

627
00:26:58,109 --> 00:26:59,834
From now on, you'll mostly be seeing

628
00:27:00,035 --> 00:27:01,620
arted spaces and lit spaces.

629
00:27:03,204 --> 00:27:04,665
So here's the same puzzle space,

630
00:27:04,705 --> 00:27:06,206
the same kind of area we've been looking at,

631
00:27:06,467 --> 00:27:08,108
but with the first art pass, for instance.

632
00:27:08,789 --> 00:27:10,610
Now there's still design changes happening here.

633
00:27:10,670 --> 00:27:14,033
For instance, we wanted to pull you here to this obstruction

634
00:27:14,073 --> 00:27:16,114
to see the second gene lock door in the distance

635
00:27:16,254 --> 00:27:18,857
more closely, and so we moved the door,

636
00:27:18,957 --> 00:27:21,298
the entrance to that command center, around the corner

637
00:27:21,779 --> 00:27:23,300
so that you wouldn't be drawn to it

638
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:25,422
before you were drawn to this big obstruction

639
00:27:25,462 --> 00:27:26,322
in the middle of the hallway.

640
00:27:26,763 --> 00:27:28,644
Then here's that same command center space

641
00:27:28,925 --> 00:27:30,466
with the deeper water that I just showed you,

642
00:27:30,606 --> 00:27:31,246
but with an art pass.

643
00:27:33,605 --> 00:27:34,566
So, the swim labs.

644
00:27:35,867 --> 00:27:36,628
For several play tests,

645
00:27:36,648 --> 00:27:38,470
the feedback on the swimming parts of the level

646
00:27:38,510 --> 00:27:39,491
had been pretty negative.

647
00:27:39,971 --> 00:27:42,213
But we really believed in this type of experience

648
00:27:42,894 --> 00:27:43,995
that we were trying to present.

649
00:27:44,495 --> 00:27:45,956
And we felt that it was the swimming system,

650
00:27:45,996 --> 00:27:47,057
the idea of swimming underwater,

651
00:27:47,097 --> 00:27:48,479
that needed some iteration time,

652
00:27:48,499 --> 00:27:49,940
that needed some time to be developed.

653
00:27:50,861 --> 00:27:52,542
At a certain point, the core design team

654
00:27:53,535 --> 00:27:55,537
came to us with revised guidelines and metrics

655
00:27:55,577 --> 00:27:57,679
for how swimming spaces should work.

656
00:27:58,359 --> 00:28:00,061
And unfortunately, this was right in the middle

657
00:28:00,081 --> 00:28:02,524
of the art pass, so we had to rush to try to adjust

658
00:28:02,564 --> 00:28:04,005
to some new metrics and ideas.

659
00:28:04,926 --> 00:28:08,209
So the vision was underwater swimming should be smooth,

660
00:28:08,289 --> 00:28:11,372
fluid, fast, it shouldn't focus on slowed movement,

661
00:28:11,532 --> 00:28:13,634
oxygen deprivation, stress, darkness.

662
00:28:14,715 --> 00:28:16,898
Unfortunately, this is a lot of what we were doing.

663
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:22,742
So, just as an example, they made a whole bunch of videos

664
00:28:22,802 --> 00:28:25,404
of like, don't do this using parts of my level.

665
00:28:29,327 --> 00:28:30,908
Yeah.

666
00:28:31,168 --> 00:28:33,730
Avoid bad flows, avoid using hard-edged geometry,

667
00:28:35,010 --> 00:28:37,452
avoid placing tricky doorways and openings.

668
00:28:38,573 --> 00:28:40,594
This is that tight space that you swam through earlier

669
00:28:40,634 --> 00:28:41,295
that I pointed out.

670
00:28:43,316 --> 00:28:44,737
Provide clear player direction.

671
00:28:46,218 --> 00:28:52,940
So, we took another stab at changing the metrics in the swim labs, the most important change

672
00:28:52,980 --> 00:28:56,281
of which was we doubled the depth and doubled the width of everything.

673
00:28:56,541 --> 00:28:58,221
And we had to do that in the middle of the art pass.

674
00:28:58,702 --> 00:29:02,022
Here is the same space with an art pass with a lighting pass.

675
00:29:03,403 --> 00:29:05,723
And as you can see, everything is much deeper, much wider.

676
00:29:07,275 --> 00:29:09,616
Now, this wasn't the most popular change.

677
00:29:10,156 --> 00:29:12,456
It kind of strained credulity that we had a bunker

678
00:29:12,516 --> 00:29:16,177
with ceilings that were like 12 meters high, 20 meters high.

679
00:29:17,097 --> 00:29:19,578
But I think that when you see the space in practice,

680
00:29:19,738 --> 00:29:23,238
it doesn't really, it doesn't strike you as being that odd.

681
00:29:23,558 --> 00:29:25,759
But now you can see in here, we're getting much closer

682
00:29:25,799 --> 00:29:27,199
to the right feeling, the right vibe, right?

683
00:29:27,259 --> 00:29:29,319
Holographic lighting, darkness.

684
00:29:30,339 --> 00:29:31,780
This is that tight hallway section.

685
00:29:31,840 --> 00:29:33,780
I stripped a whole bunch of the obstacles out of it

686
00:29:33,820 --> 00:29:34,960
so it was easier to swim through.

687
00:29:36,362 --> 00:29:39,303
But players were still dealing with oxygen deprivation stress, right?

688
00:29:39,323 --> 00:29:41,864
They didn't feel like they could just swim through this section easily.

