00:30:35,003 --> 00:30:36,904
this was sort of my North Star concept art piece

711
00:30:36,944 --> 00:30:37,984
but we decided to ditch this.

712
00:30:38,764 --> 00:30:41,225
This spider looks too much like a machine out in the world

713
00:30:41,325 --> 00:30:44,407
and it needs to look like something in an old world bunker.

714
00:30:44,447 --> 00:30:45,627
It needs to look like old world tech.

715
00:30:46,487 --> 00:30:47,808
So we moved in this direction.

716
00:30:48,248 --> 00:30:50,389
This was something that we actually kid bashed together

717
00:30:50,409 --> 00:30:52,130
with a whole bunch of old bunker pieces.

718
00:30:54,853 --> 00:30:55,734
So let me show you that.

719
00:30:57,675 --> 00:31:00,076
So this is the first like built out of art pieces

720
00:31:00,136 --> 00:31:03,498
version of the spider with actual physics derived chains

721
00:31:03,578 --> 00:31:04,898
and stuff like this, you'll see.

722
00:31:14,503 --> 00:31:16,804
Now we still have the tutorial moment here,

723
00:31:17,324 --> 00:31:19,025
but you'll see the weak points have changed a bit.

724
00:31:20,163 --> 00:31:22,704
We added this new idea which was a timing element.

725
00:31:22,904 --> 00:31:24,385
So you couldn't just run around the whole room

726
00:31:24,405 --> 00:31:26,246
and yoink all the covers off, shoot all the things.

727
00:31:26,827 --> 00:31:28,688
Now it was based on the movement of the spider,

728
00:31:28,748 --> 00:31:30,909
whether those weak points would be exposed to you or not.

729
00:31:38,834 --> 00:31:40,054
Boss is still pretty much the same,

