00:34:39,975 --> 00:34:43,499
to make a pitch for a bold reinvention of Death's Door.

801
00:34:44,279 --> 00:34:46,241
Shortly thereafter, the heads of the studio reached out

802
00:34:46,261 --> 00:34:48,843
to let us know that we were shifting the entire company

803
00:34:49,144 --> 00:34:51,606
to a remote working model in response to a new pandemic.

804
00:34:52,246 --> 00:34:53,628
I think you all know how that went.

805
00:34:54,975 --> 00:34:56,897
For the foreseeable future, Gorilla would be working

806
00:34:56,937 --> 00:34:59,858
from home and my task was to come up with a bold new pitch.

807
00:35:01,900 --> 00:35:04,421
So why did we go about doing a rework?

808
00:35:04,621 --> 00:35:06,282
Let me talk for a moment about Ace Pillars.

809
00:35:07,523 --> 00:35:10,005
So Ace was a tool that we started using in this time

810
00:35:10,045 --> 00:35:12,606
to help us identify shortcomings in the design of the game.

811
00:35:13,644 --> 00:35:14,965
A is for astonishing.

812
00:35:15,526 --> 00:35:19,049
We felt collectively like the content in the early part of the bunker wasn't astonishing

813
00:35:19,089 --> 00:35:19,309
enough.

814
00:35:19,489 --> 00:35:22,671
It didn't equal some of the wow moments in bunkers in the first game.

815
00:35:23,112 --> 00:35:26,535
Think about the giant Titan room in the Grave Horde, for instance.

816
00:35:27,796 --> 00:35:28,896
C is for challenging.

817
00:35:29,057 --> 00:35:31,999
The puzzles in the swim section weren't challenging players enough.

818
00:35:32,299 --> 00:35:33,280
Frustrating, yes.

819
00:35:33,560 --> 00:35:34,361
Challenging, no.

820
00:35:35,862 --> 00:35:36,844
E is for engaging.

821
00:35:37,084 --> 00:35:39,347
We weren't making full use of the suite of new tools

822
00:35:39,387 --> 00:35:40,348
at Aloy's disposal.

823
00:35:40,688 --> 00:35:43,412
We wanted to add some of the new Forbidden West mechanics

824
00:35:43,572 --> 00:35:45,674
here like the shield wing and the grappling hook.

825
00:35:47,457 --> 00:35:50,781
So, I started off by outlining a new set of goals

826
00:35:50,921 --> 00:35:53,224
informed by those conversations and feedback.

827
00:35:54,682 --> 00:35:56,844
The goals were provide an astonishing moment

828
00:35:56,924 --> 00:35:58,225
shortly after entering the bunker,

829
00:35:58,605 --> 00:36:00,727
focus on challenging traversal gameplay

830
00:36:01,367 --> 00:36:03,769
through an epic space using grappling, pulling, and gliding,

831
00:36:04,289 --> 00:36:05,410
give the player a clear sense

832
00:36:05,450 --> 00:36:06,651
that they're moving towards a goal,

833
00:36:06,831 --> 00:36:08,052
that is the second gene locked door,

834
00:36:08,072 --> 00:36:09,273
while progressing through the space.

835
00:36:09,994 --> 00:36:11,895
I also outlined a set of limitations.

836
00:36:13,291 --> 00:36:15,452
Shrink the square footage for the purpose of art and lighting.

837
00:36:15,632 --> 00:36:17,553
The zenith must be able to navigate the space

838
00:36:17,593 --> 00:36:19,414
where they follow you in, those are the bad guys.

839
00:36:20,074 --> 00:36:22,195
And we need to maintain the communication center

840
00:36:22,395 --> 00:36:24,917
and Traff's room, that office at the end of the swim labs,

841
00:36:25,257 --> 00:36:28,298
as locations for the player where they have to experience

842
00:36:28,358 --> 00:36:29,779
essential storytelling moments.

843
00:36:30,539 --> 00:36:32,420
Now it's important to have goals and limitations

844
00:36:32,480 --> 00:36:34,001
because you have to sell both.

845
00:36:34,781 --> 00:36:36,002
When you come up with a new pitch,

846
00:36:36,382 --> 00:36:38,043
you have to get the people you're pitching to

847
00:36:38,063 --> 00:36:39,744
to understand the goals and limitations

848
00:36:39,784 --> 00:36:42,525
so they understand how your pitch matches those needs.

849
00:36:44,200 --> 00:36:46,042
So here's the pitch, I've grayed out most of it

